s and rocket launches. \n\nIn the United States, NASA Television's Public and Media channels are MPEG-2 digital C-band signals carried by DVB-S2/8PSK modulation on satellite Galaxy 13, transponder 15, at 127 degrees west longitude. Downlink frequency is 4009.00 MHz, horizontal polarization, with a data rate of 36.225 Mbps, symbol rate of 15.000 Msps, and 5/6 FEC. A Digital Video Broadcast (DVB-S2) compliant Integrated Receiver Decoder (IRD) is needed for reception.","commandRuns":[{"startIndex":338,"length":22,"onTap":{"innertubeCommand":{"clickTrackingParams":"CBIQ040EGAUiEwiItc7Y5NyVAxUeZ50GHeS1D8NI-POMysay_qrbAcoBBAS13vs=","commandMetadata":{"webCommandMetadata":{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/redirect?event=video_description\u0026redir_token=QUFFLUhqa1E3dk5sTl9Qb2gtNHgteTBmMzVHOU5zVVVId3xBQ3Jtc0tsVldOT25QdjZ6MlhIMlVJX2g3WGFoU0JmdF9pVDV0V19ZUndEX1gydGptT2RPakt6QW5pVmNPMTRMajJ0a25feXMyVU5UQ0JoaVA5ZGV4Z1B2YWU5dHJ3dlJSWFlVQy0yUlRMZUZvSjhmMW4zMUZzcw\u0026q=https%3A%2F%2Fplus.nasa.gov%2F\u0026v=21X5lGlDOfg","webPageType":"WEB_PAGE_TYPE_UNKNOWN","rootVe":83769}},"urlEndpoint":{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/redirect?event=video_description\u0026redir_token=QUFFLUhqa1E3dk5sTl9Qb2gtNHgteTBmMzVHOU5zVVVId3xBQ3Jtc0tsVldOT25QdjZ6MlhIMlVJX2g3WGFoU0JmdF9pVDV0V19ZUndEX1gydGptT2RPakt6QW5pVmNPMTRMajJ0a25feXMyVU5UQ0JoaVA5ZGV4Z1B2YWU5dHJ3dlJSWFlVQy0yUlRMZUZvSjhmMW4zMUZzcw\u0026q=https%3A%2F%2Fplus.nasa.gov%2F\u0026v=21X5lGlDOfg","target":"TARGET_NEW_WINDOW","nofollow":true}}}}],"styleRuns":[{"startIndex":0,"length":79,"styleRunExtensions":{"styleRunColorMapExtension":{"colorMap":[{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_DARK","value":4294634464},{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_LIGHT","value":4281736458}]}},"fontFamilyName":"Roboto"},{"startIndex":79,"length":13,"fontName":"Roboto-Medium","weightLabel":"FONT_WEIGHT_BOLD","styleRunExtensions":{"styleRunColorMapExtension":{"colorMap":[{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_DARK","value":4294634464},{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_LIGHT","value":4281736458}]}},"f